# SillyTavern Docker Setup with Ollama

This Docker Compose setup runs SillyTavern with persistent data storage and Ollama integration.

## Prerequisites

- Docker and Docker Compose installed
- Ollama installed and running on your Mac ([https://ollama.com/](https://ollama.com/))
- At least one Ollama model pulled (e.g., `ollama pull llama2`)

## Quick Start

### 1. Start SillyTavern

```bash
docker compose up -d
```

This will:
- Pull the latest SillyTavern image
- Create persistent volumes in the current directory
- Start the container in the background

### 2. Access SillyTavern

Open your browser and navigate to:
```
http://localhost:8000
```

### 3. Connect to Ollama

1. In SillyTavern, click the **plug icon** (top-right) to open API Connections
2. Select **Chat Completion** sources
3. Choose **Text Completion** or **Chat Completion** API
4. Set the API URL to:
   ```
   http://host.docker.internal:11434
   ```
5. Click **Connect**
6. Select your Ollama model from the dropdown

## Directory Structure

All persistent data is stored in subdirectories:

```
docker_silly/
├── docker-compose.yml    # Docker Compose configuration
├── .env                  # Environment variables
├── README.md            # This file
├── config/              # SillyTavern configuration files
├── data/                # User data (chats, characters, etc.)
├── plugins/             # Installed plugins
└── extensions/          # Third-party extensions
```

